Title: Representations of The Coordinate Ring of $GL_{q}(3)$
Authors: Vahid Karimipour
Comments: pages 20
Report-no: 93-010
Journal-ref: J.Phys. A26 (1993) L957-L962
\\
  It is shown that the finite dimensional ireducible representations of the
quantum matrix algebra $ M_q(3) $ ( the coordinate ring of $ GL_q(3) $ ) exist
only when q is a root of unity ( $ q^p = 1 $ ). The dimensions of these
representations can only be one of the following values: $ p^3 , { p^3 \over 2
} , { p^3 \over 4 } $ or $ { p^3 \over 8 } $ . The topology of the space of
states ranges between two extremes , from a 3-dimensional torus $ S^1 \times
S^1 \times S^1 $ ( which may be thought of as a generalization of the cyclic
representation ) to a 3-dimensional cube $ [ 0 , 1 ]\times [ 0 , 1 ]\times
[ 0 , 1 ] $ .
